*Triangles* — sides $a, b, c$, semiperimeter $p = (a+b+c) \/ 2$

$ A = sqrt(p(p-a)(p-b)(p-c)) $
$ R = (a b c) / (4A), quad r = A / p $
$ m_a = 1/2 sqrt(2b^2 + 2c^2 - a^2), quad s_a = sqrt(b c [1 - (a / (b+c))^2]) $

*Law of sines:*
$ (sin alpha) / a = (sin beta) / b = (sin gamma) / c = 1 / (2R) $

*Law of cosines:* #h(1em) $a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2 b c cos alpha$

*Law of tangents:*
$ (a+b) / (a-b) = tan((alpha+beta) \/ 2) / tan((alpha-beta) \/ 2) $

*Quadrilaterals* — sides $a,b,c,d$, diags $e,f$, diag angle $theta$, $F = b^2+d^2-a^2-c^2$
$ 4A = 2 e f sin theta = F tan theta = sqrt(4 e^2 f^2 - F^2) $
Cyclic: opposite angles sum $180degree$, $e f = a c + b d$, $A = sqrt((p-a)(p-b)(p-c)(p-d))$.

